<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8f01e101-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1464"><num value="1464">§ 1464.</num><heading> Voice of America/Europe</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As part of its duties and programs under this subchapter, Voice of America/Europe shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8f01e102-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1464/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> target news and features in accordance with the findings and recommendations of the Young European Survey;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8f01e103-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1464/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> conduct periodic audience evaluations and measurements; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id8f01e104-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s1464/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> promote and advertise Voice of America/Europe.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id8f01e105-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-01-27/ch36">Jan. 27, 1948, ch. 36</ref>, title V, § 504, as added <ref href="/us/pl/100/204/tIV/s402">Pub. L. 100–204, title IV, § 402</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1381">101 Stat. 1381</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
